International tuna bodies are demanding catch limits to prevent overfishing and save the declining tuna population.
Japan, the world's top tuna consumer, faces pressure from environmentalists for driving tuna to extinction.
The call for a moratorium on large tuna vessels aims to ensure sustainable tuna fishing.
Conservation bodies are pushing for a global action plan to monitor and control tuna fishing.
The focus is on reversing the decline in tuna stocks through better management and cooperation among international organizations.
Efforts are underway to address overfishing and poaching to secure the future of tuna resources.
